N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 120.1 - Brand definition

State Regulations

Soil or plant inoculants and seeds or fertilizers
inoculated with a culture of a specific microorganism, or a mixture of
microorganisms, shall be deemed to be separate and distinct brands when
differing either in name, brand or trademark, or in any other label
characteristic. Notes
